This press briefing is about the stalemate in Congress regarding the FAA bill, which has led to nearly 4,000 FAA employees being furloughed and 70,000 construction workers being out of work. Transportation Secretary Ray LaHood speaks about the negative impact this has on the economy and jobs, and calls on Congress to pass a clean bill to resolve the issue. Press Secretary Jay Carney takes questions on the debt ceiling negotiations and emphasizes the need for a compromise to avoid default and protect the economy. He also discusses the possibility of a grand bargain and the importance of lifting the debt ceiling beyond the holiday season to avoid economic uncertainty. Carney emphasizes that the priority is to protect the economy and the American people from harm.